The youths within Kisumu County have castigated Kisumu central MP Fred Ouda over his utterance, and allegations against governor Anyang Nyong’o in relations to the recently concluded nominations. Ouda alleged that if one was not aligned to governor Nyong’o, they will lose in the exercise. “I want to tell the governor that what you did was wrong, I have forgiven you, I will not interfere with you but kindly look for your own votes, “he said However,  the youths under the umbrella ’Kisumu county Youth for Change’ condemned the malicious attempt to drag the name of the governor in such politics. Led by their chairperson George Ochieng, Martin Odhiambo and Ruth Owitty, they told Ouda to stop antagonizing the people of Kisumu and by extension tarnishing the name of the governor. “We want to condemn in the strongest term possible the malicious attempt to drag the name of our governor in divisive politics during this electioneer period, "said Odhiambo He noted that as association they  don’t expect any person of goodwill for the people of Kisumu to antagonize the interest of voters. While supporting the issuance of direct ticked to Nyong’o, the youths noted that  it was a wise decision by the ODM party that will see the governor continue with his development project once re-elected for a second term. They noted that their decision to back Nyong’o is anchored on the reputable development track record hat has been evident across the whole county. “Infrastructural development, a case study of the transformation of Kisumu city from the them squalor to now a magnificent golden sparking ‘yurop’." He added that there has been improved status of feeder roads at the sub county levels moreover through his propensity leadership, and governance he also managed to lobby resources for the construction of Mamboleo-Chemelil-Muhoroni road.